The paper deals with enhancing real-world depth images using computer vision techniques, which suggests that it belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a low-cost sensor, which could fall under the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of a Tri-Cycle loss, which could suggest that it belongs to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The use of a Cycle-GAN could also suggest that it belongs to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with unsupervised domain translation, which could suggest that it belongs to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
